article.description: Ben Wallace set an NBA season high with 28 rebounds, scored 13 points and blocked six shots as the Detroit Pistons beat the Boston Celtics 109-101 Sunday.
article.headline: Wallace makes pitch for defensive honors

images.name: Wallace_Ben 032402 inline
images.caption: More impressive than this slam for Ben Wallace was his 28 rebounds, the best in the NBA this season.

article.linkText: Wallace pulls down 28 boards as Pistons top Celtics
article.story:
AUBURN HILLS, Mich. (AP) -- Joe Dumars said the secret is out about one of the league's best dirty-work players. Ben Wallace set an NBA season high with 28 rebounds, scored 13 points and blocked six shots as the Detroit Pistons beat the Boston Celtics 109-101 Sunday. "This was definitely his coming-out party," said Dumars, the Pistons' president and former star shooting guard. "People saw what he's been doing for us for two years." Each time Wallace grabbed a rebound, a white T-shirt with a red 'R' was handed out to fans in the fourth row behind the scorers' table. "I wanted to wrap those T-shirts all around the arena," Wallace said with a grin. "But I think they were running out, so I slowed down." The Pistons are showing no signs of slowing down the momentum they began to pick up two months ago. They have won 22 of 30 games, and five of six. "It's a great story to talk about how we don't have respect, but we're not worried about that," Detroit's Jerry Stackhouse said. "People will catch on sooner or later." Stackhouse had 30 points, eight assists and eight rebounds and Cliff Robinson had 20 points and seven assists. Chucky Atkins added 17 for Detroit, which kept its comfortable lead in the Central Division and stayed close to New Jersey for the best record in the Eastern Conference. Paul Pierce scored 35 and Antoine Walker had 28 for Boston, which has lost four of five. "We can't get too down about this," Pierce said. "But we also can't give Ben Wallace get 28 rebounds. He's a terror, he just attacks. He's a great player, and I don't think he gets the credit he deserves." Wallace, who matched his career-high total for rebounds, might have strengthened his chances of being the league's defensive player of the year after Detroit's first nationally televised game on NBC in two years. Celtics coach Jim O'Brien said he couldn't think of anybody more deserving than Wallace to win the award, and Boston's Tony Battie agreed. "He's the defensive player of the year, hands down," said Battie, who added that Wallace is this era's Dennis Rodman. Detroit took command of the game with a 15-0 run in the third quarter to take a 79-66 lead. The Celtics scored nine consecutive points midway through the fourth to pull to eight down, but couldn't get closer than five. Detroit got off to a great start and never looked sluggish despite returning from a five-game road trip less than 30 hours before the tipoff Sunday. The Pistons led 10-1 after a few minutes and 32-22 after the first quarter. The Celtics outscored Detroit 21-8 midway through the second quarter and took a 51-50 lead with 2:22 left in the half. The Pistons led 56-53 at halftime. After a few lead changes and a couple ties, Detroit's big run led to a 82-70 lead after three quarters. "That was huge because it gave us the cushion we needed," Detroit coach Rick Carlisle said. "Our crowd got energized and we were really making shots, and stops." Game notes
Boston's Kenny Anderson limped off the floor with a sprained left ankle late in the third, and said he's day-to-day. ... Wallace is 13 blocks away from matching Bob Lanier's franchise record of 247, set during the 1973-74 season. ... Detroit is 10-0 when Stackhouse and Robinson score at least 20 each and 19-0 when it scores 100 or more. ... After going 4-1 on a road trip, the Pistons arrived home from Los Angeles at about 8 a.m. Saturday -- a turnaround Wallace called the toughest turnaround of his career. ... Eight of Detroit's final 13 games are at home, while seven of Boston's last 12 will be home games. ... Memphis' Lorenzen Wright had the NBA's previous season high with 28 rebounds against Dallas on Nov. 4. ...
